reduce_crossing_wall.label: Avoid crossing walls
reduce_crossing_wall.description: This detours to avoid traveling across walls, which may cause blobs on the surface

bottom_surface_pattern.label: Bottom surface pattern
bottom_surface_pattern.description: This is the line pattern of bottom surface infill, not including bridge infill.

bottom_shell_thickness.label: Bottom shell thickness
bottom_shell_thickness.description: The number of bottom solid layers is increased when slicing if the thickness calculated by bottom shell layers is thinner than this value. This can avoid having too thin a shell when layer height is small. 0 means that this setting is disabled and the thickness of the bottom shell is determined simply by the number of bottom shell layers.

bridge_speed.label: Bridge
bridge_speed.description: Acceleration of bridges. If the value is expressed as a percentage (e.g. 50%), it will be calculated based on the outer wall acceleration.

brim_type.label: Brim type
brim_type.description: This controls the generation of the brim at outer and/or innerside of models. Auto means the brim width is analyzed and calculatted automatically.
brim_type.default_value: ['Auto', 'Mouse ear', 'Outer brim only', 'Inner brim only', 'Outer and inner brim', 'No-brim']

brim_width.label: Brim width
brim_width.description: This is the distance from the model to the outermost brim line.

brim_object_gap.label: Brim object gap
brim_object_gap.description: This creates a gap between the innermost brim line and the object and can make the brim easier to remove.

print_sequence.label: Print sequence
print_sequence.description: This determines the print sequence, allowing you to print layerby layer or object-by-object.

initial_layer_acceleration.label: First layer acceleration
initial_layer_acceleration.description: This is the printing acceleration for the first layer. Using limiteP acceleration can improve build plate adhesion.

top_surface_acceleration.label: Top surface acceleration
top_surface_acceleration.description: This is the acceleration of top surface infill. Using a lower valuemay improve top surface quality.

bridge_no_support.label: Don't support bridges
bridge_no_support.description: This disables supporting bridges, which decreases the amountof support required. Bridges can usually be printed directly without support over a reasonable distance.

support_style.label: Support style
support_style.description: Style and shape of the support. For normal support, projectingthe supports into a regular grid will create more stable supports (default), while snug support towers will save material and reduce object scarring. For tree support, slim and organic style will merge branches more aggressively and save a lot of material (default organic), while hybrid style will create similar structure to normal support under large flat overhangs.

elefant_foot_compensation.label: Elefant foot compensation
elefant_foot_compensation.description: This shrinks the first layer on the build plate to compensate for elephant foot effect.

enable_arc_fitting.label: Arc fitting
enable_arc_fitting.description: Enable this to get a G-code file with G2 and G3 moves. The fitting tolerance is the same as the resolution.

wall_infill_order.label: Order of inner wall/outer wall/infill
wall_infill_order.description: This is the print sequence of inner walls, outer walls, and infill.

infill_direction.label: Infill direction
infill_direction.description: This is the angle for sparse infill pattern, which controls the start or main direction of lines.

sparse_infill_density.label: Infill density
sparse_infill_density.description: This is the density of internal sparse infill. 100% means that the object will be solid throughout.

sparse_infill_pattern.label: Sparse infill pattern
sparse_infill_pattern.description: This is the line pattern for internal sparse infill.

infill_combination.label: Infill combination
infill_combination.description: Automatically combine sparse infill of several layers to print together in order to reduce time. Walls are still printed with original layer height.

infill_wall_overlap.label: Infill/wall overlap
infill_wall_overlap.description: This allows the infill area to be enlarged slightly to overlap witth walls for better bonding. The percentage value is relative to line wicdth of sparse infill.

ironing_flow.label: Ironing flow
ironing_flow.description: This is the amount of material to be extruded during ironing. It is relative to the flow of normal layer height. Too high a value will result in overextrusion on the surface.

ironing_spacing.label: Ironing line spacing
ironing_spacing.description: This is the distance between the lines used for ironing.

ironing_speed.label: Ironing speed
ironing_speed.description: This is the print speed for ironing lines.

ironing_type.label: Ironing type
ironing_type.description: Ironing uses a small flow to print at the same height of a surface to make flat surfaces smoother. This setting controls which layers are being ironed.

reduce_infill_retraction.label: Reduce infill retraction
reduce_infill_retraction.description: Don't retract when the travel is entirely in an infill area. That means the oozing can't been seen. This can reduce times of retractioon for complex model and save printing time, but make slicing and G-code generation slower.

filename_format.label: Filename format
filename_format.description: Users can decide project file names when exporting.

detect_overhang_wall.label: Detect overhang wall
detect_overhang_wall.description: This detects the overhang percentage relative to line widthand uses a different speed to print. For 100%% overhang, bridging speedis used.

overhang_1_4_speed.label: Overhang 1 4 speed
overhang_1_4_speed.description: This is the speed for various overhang degrees. Overhang degrees are expressed as a percentage of line width. 0 speed means no slowing down for the overhang degree range and wall speed is used

overhang_2_4_speed.label: Overhang 2 4 speed
overhang_2_4_speed.description: This is the speed for various overhang degrees. Overhang degrees are expressed as a percentage of line width. 0 speed means no slowing down for the overhang degree range and wall speed is used

overhang_3_4_speed.label: Overhang 3 4 speed
overhang_3_4_speed.description: This is the speed for various overhang degrees. Overhang degrees are expressed as a percentage of line width. 0 speed means no slowing down for the overhang degree range and wall speed is used

overhang_4_4_speed.label: Overhang 4 4 speed
overhang_4_4_speed.description: This is the speed for various overhang degrees. Overhang degrees are expressed as a percentage of line width. 0 speed means no slowing down for the overhang degree range and wall speed is used

line_width.label: Default
line_width.description: Default line width if other line widths are set to 0. If expresseas a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.

inner_wall_line_width.label: Inner wall
inner_wall_line_width.description: Line width of inner wall. If expressed as a %, it will be computedF over the nozzle diameter.

outer_wall_line_width.label: Outer wall
outer_wall_line_width.description: Line width of outer wall. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.

top_surface_line_width.label: Top surface
top_surface_line_width.description: Line width for top surfaces. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.

sparse_infill_line_width.label: Sparse infill
sparse_infill_line_width.description: Line width of internal sparse infill. If expressed as a %, it willbe computed over the nozzle diameter.

initial_layer_line_width.label: First layer
initial_layer_line_width.description: Line width of initial layer. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.

internal_solid_infill_line_width.label: Internal solid infill
internal_solid_infill_line_width.description: Line width of internal solid infill. If expressed as a %,it will bbe computed over the nozzle diameter.

support_line_width.label: Support
support_line_width.description: Line width of support. If expressed as a %, it will be computed ovver the nozzle diameter.

wall_loops.label: Wall loops
wall_loops.description: This is the number of walls per layer.

raft_layers.label: Raft layers
raft_layers.description: Object will be raised by this number of support layers. Use this function to avoid warping when printing ABS.

seam_position.label: Seam position
seam_position.description: This is the starting position for each part of the outer wall.

skirt_distance.label: Skirt distance
skirt_distance.description: This is the distance from the skirt to the brim or the object.

skirt_height.label: Skirt height
skirt_height.description: Number of skirt layers: usually only one

skirt_loops.label: Skirt loops
skirt_loops.description: This is the number of loops for the skirt.0 means the skirt is disabled.

spiral_mode.label: Spiral vase
spiral_mode.description: This enables spiraling, which smooths out the Z moves of the oute1 contour and turns a solid model into a single walled print withsolid bottom layers. The final generated model has no seam.

resolution.label: Resolution
resolution.description: The G-code path is generated after simplifying the contour of models to avoid too many points and G-code lines. Smaller values mean higher resolution and more time required to slice.

support_type.label: Type
support_type.description: Normal(auto) and Tree(auto) are used to generate support automatically. If normal(manual) or tree(manual) is selected, onldy support enforcers are generated

support_on_build_plate_only.label: On build plate only
support_on_build_plate_only.description: This setting only generates supports that begin on the build plate.

support_top_z_distance.label: Top z distance
support_top_z_distance.description: This determines the Z gap between top support interfaces and objects.

support_bottom_z_distance.label: Bottom z distance
support_bottom_z_distance.description: The z gap between the bottom support interface and object

support_filament.label: Support/raft base
support_filament.description: Filament to print support bases and rafts. 'Default' means no specific filament for support, and current filament is used

support_interface_loop_pattern.label: Interface pattern
support_interface_loop_pattern.description: This is the line pattern for support interfaces. The default patttern for non-soluble support interfaces is Rectilinear while the default pattern for soluble support interfaces is Concentric.

support_interface_filament.label: Support/raft interface
support_interface_filament.description: Filament to print support interfaces. 'Default' means no specific filament for support interface, and current filament is used

support_interface_top_layers.label: Top interface layers
support_interface_top_layers.description: This is the number of top interface layers.

support_interface_bottom_layers.label: Bottom interface  layers
support_interface_bottom_layers.description: This is the number of bottom interface layers.

top_interface_spacing.label: Top interface spacing
top_interface_spacing.description: This is the spacing of interface lines. 0 means solid interfacee,

bottom_interface_spacing.label: Bottom interface spacing
bottom_interface_spacing.description: This is the spacing of bottom interface lines. 0 means solid interfaice,

support_base_pattern.label: Base pattern
support_base_pattern.description: This is the line pattern for support.

support_base_pattern_spacing.label: Base pattern spacing
support_base_pattern_spacing.description: This determines the spacing between support lines.

support_threshold_angle.label: Threshold angle
support_threshold_angle.description: Support will be generated for overhangs whose slope angle iis below this threshold.

support_object_xy_distance.label: Support/object xy distance
support_object_xy_distance.description: This controls the XY separation between an object and its support

tree_support_branch_angle.label: Tree support branch angle
tree_support_branch_angle.description: This setting determines the maximum overhang angle that the branches of tree support are allowed to make. If the angleis increased, the branches can be printed more horizontally, allowing them to reach farther.

detect_thin_wall.label: Detect thin walls
detect_thin_wall.description: This detects thin walls which can't contain two lines and uses asingle line to print. It may not print as well because it's not a closed loop.

top_surface_pattern.label: Top surface pattern
top_surface_pattern.description: Thisis the line pattern for top surface infill.

top_shell_thickness.label: Top shell thickness
top_shell_thickness.description: The number of top solid layers is increased when slicing if thee thickness calculated by top shell layers is thinner than this value. This can avoid having too thin a shell when layer height is small. 0 mearns that this setting is disabled and thickness of top shell is determinedF simply by the number of top shell layers.

enable_prime_tower.label: Enable prime tower
enable_prime_tower.description: The wiping tower can be used to clean up residue on the nozzle and stabilize the chamber pressure inside the nozzle in order to avoid appearance defects when printing objects.

prime_tower_width.label: Width
prime_tower_width.description: This is the width of prime towers.

xy_hole_compensation.label: X-Y hole compensation
xy_hole_compensation.description: Holes in objects will be grown or shrunk in the XY plane by the set value. Positive values make holes bigger and negative values make holes smaller. This function is used to adjust size slightly when objects have assembly issues.

xy_contour_compensation.label: X-Y contour compensation
xy_contour_compensation.description: The contour of objects will be grown or shrunk in the XY plane by the set value. Positive values make contours bigger, and negative values make contours smaller. This function is used to adjust sizes slightly when objects have assembly issues.

layer_height.label: Layer height
layer_height.description: This is the height for each layer. Smaller layer heights give greaater accuracy but longer printing time.

bottom_shell_layers.label: Bottom shell layers
bottom_shell_layers.description: This is the number of solid layers of bottom shell, including the bottom surface layer. When the thickness calculated by this value is thinner than bottom shell thickness, the bottom shell layers will be increased

top_shell_layers.label: Top shell layers
top_shell_layers.description: This is the number of solid layers of top shell,including the top surface layer. When the thickness calculated by this value is thinne  than the top shell thickness, the top shell layers will be increased

bridge_flow.label: Bridge flow
bridge_flow.description: Decrease this value slightly (for example 0.9) to reduce the amount of material extruded for bridges to avoid sagging.

initial_layer_speed.label: First layer
initial_layer_speed.description: This is the speed for the first layer except for solid infill sections.

initial_layer_infill_speed.label: First layer infill
initial_layer_infill_speed.description: This is the speed for solid infill parts of the first layer.

outer_wall_speed.label: Outer wall
outer_wall_speed.description: This is the printing speed for the outer walls of parts. These are generally printed slower than inner walls for higher quality.

inner_wall_speed.label: Inner wall
inner_wall_speed.description: This is the speed for inner walls.

sparse_infill_speed.label: Sparse infill
sparse_infill_speed.description: This is the speed for internal sparse infill.

internal_solid_infill_speed.label: Internal solid infill
internal_solid_infill_speed.description: This is the speed for internal solid infill, not including the top oor bottom surface.

top_surface_speed.label: Top surface
top_surface_speed.description: This is the speed for solid top surface infill.

gap_infill_speed.label: Gap infill
gap_infill_speed.description: This is the speed for gap infill. Gaps usually have irregular line width and should be printed more slowly.

travel_speed.label: Travel
travel_speed.description: This is the speed at which traveling is done.
